Sentencas: In this paper, Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) nanoparticles modified GdBaCo2O5+delta (GBCO) cathodes were fabricated by an infiltration technique and evaluated for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Nanosized Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 infiltrated GdBaCo2O5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Good chemical compatibility between GBCO and infiltrated SDC was confirmed by X-ray diffraction (XRD) characterization.
Titulo: Nanosized Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 infiltrated GdBaCo2O5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SDC nanoparticles (similar to 40 nm) formed continuous ionic-conducting phase on porous GBCO backbone, which contributed to significantly improved electro-catalytic property.
Titulo: Nanosized Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 infiltrated GdBaCo2O5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SDC loading exhibited encouragingly low R, value of 0.1 Omega cm(2), which was much lower than 0.43 Omega cm(2) of pure-GBCO cathode.
Titulo: Nanosized Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 infiltrated GdBaCo2O5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As revealed by PO2 dependence of impedance spectra, the oxygen reduction reaction was mainly limited by charge-transfer processes.
Titulo: Nanosized Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 infiltrated GdBaCo2O5+δ cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, a stable operation of 80 h was obtained at 600 degrees C.

Sentencas: Our study implies that infiltrated GBCO cathode is very attractive for application in IT-SOFC cathode.
